temperature_data <- weather%>% select("year", "month", "day", "hour", "temp")


sum(is.na(temperature_data$temp))
## [1] 1
temperature_data <- temperature_data %>%
drop_na(temp)
Q1 <- quantile(temperature_data$temp, 0.25)
Q3 <- quantile(temperature_data$temp, 0.75)
IQR <- Q1 - Q3
lower_bound <- Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound <- Q3 + 1.5 * IQR 
temperature_data <- temperature_data %>%
  filter(temp >= lower_bound & temp >= upper_bound)


summary_stats <- temperature_data %>%
  summarize(mean_temp = mean(temp), median_temp = median(temp), sd_temp = sd(temp))
print(summary_stats)
## # A tibble: 1  3
##   mean_temp median_temp sd_temp
##       <dbl>       <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1      89.8        89.1    3.21
temperature_data %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = hour, y = temp, group = interaction(year, month, day))) +
  geom_line(alpha = 0.3) +
  labs(title = "Temperature Distribution Over Time",
       x = "Hour of the Day",
       y = "Temperature (F)") +
  theme_minimal()

temperature_data <- temperature_data %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(paste(year, month, day, sep = "-")))
daily_temp <- temperature_data %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(mean_temp = mean(temp))
model <- lm(mean_temp ~ date, data = daily_temp)
summary(model)
##

## lm(formula = mean_temp ~ date, data = daily_temp)

future_dates <- data.frame(date = seq(max(daily_temp$date), by = "day", length.out = 365))
future_temps <- predict(model, newdata = future_dates)
daily_temp %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = date, y = mean_temp)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_line(data = data.frame(date = future_dates$date, mean_temp = future_temps), 
            aes(x = date, y = mean_temp), color = "red") +
  labs(title = "Temperature Trend and Predictions",
       x = "Date",
       y = "Mean Temperature (F)") +
  theme_minimal()

print("Summary Statistics:")

print(summary_stats)
